gov.nasa.jpf.vm

Class JPF_sun_misc_Unsafe

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nasa.jpf.vm.NativePeer
      • gov.nasa.jpf.vm.JPF_sun_misc_Unsafe
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable

    public class JPF_sun_misc_Unsafe
extends NativePeer
    we don't want this class! This is a hodgepodge of stuff that shouldn't be in Java, but is handy for some hacks. The reason we have it here - very rudimentary - is that java.util.concurrent makes use of the atomic compare&swap which is in it. The choice was to duplicate a lot of relatively difficult code in the "right" class (java.util.concurrent.locks.AbstractQueuedSynchronizer) or a small amount of straight forward code in the "wrong" class (sun.misc.Unsafe). Knowing a bit about the "library chase" game, we opt for the latter <2do> this might change with better modeling of high level java.util.concurrent constructs
